{:doc
 "RATCHET — known divergences for the js target. Every entry is a corpus row
  currently flagged by bin/beagle-certify whose divergence a human classified.
  The gate FAILS on a NEW (unlisted) flagged row and on a STALE entry (listed
  but no longer flagged) — this file only shrinks; fixing a bug forces the
  fixer to delete its entry in the same commit. No commas (the file is read by
  both EDN readers and the Racket reader). Keyed by [:id :bucket].
  Categories: :bug (tracked defect) | :host-model (target-inherent semantics
  gap e.g. nix laziness) | :strictness (beagle intentionally stricter)."
